Use the standard library
This is how to do_algebra of operator and operand:
   Remember that n is operand's length
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is 0
   End when
   Remember that result is item 0 in operand
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that op is item i in operator
      Remember that x is item (sum of i and 1) in operand
      When op is "+", then:
         Remember that result is sum of result and x
      End when
      When op is "-", then:
         Remember that result is diff of result and x
      End when
      When op is "*", then:
         Remember that result is product of result and x
      End when
      When op is "/", then:
         Remember that result is quotient of result and x
      End when
      When op is "**", then:
         Remember that power is 1
         Remember that j is 0
         Do this x times:
            Remember that power is product of power and result
            Increase j
         End do
         Remember that result is power
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know